               aggregate-resolution-metric, fire-fanout-max-concurrent
@END

@R schema-guard-update-sketch
  target /Users/ghost/core/hive/tool/blocker_autofire_lint.hexa
  current state lints required: slug, fire-cmd, omega-stop, resolution-{metric,op,value} or resolution-fallback, why, attempts-log
  new lint rules
    R1 if fire-parallel-fanout present:
       - fire-cmd MAY be absent (mutex with fanout) — relax existing have_fire check
       - require aggregate-resolution-metric ∈ {all-pass, any-pass, quorum-N}
       - require fire-fanout-max-concurrent > 0 (default 3 acceptable)
    R2 if fire-fanout-deps present without fire-parallel-fanout → lint error (orphan deps)
    R3 fire-fanout-deps format "i:j[,i:j]*" — validate indices < len(fanout_list)
    R4 detect cycles statically (warning only — runtime guard is authoritative)
  test scenarios (if no schema-guard yet — propose)
    T1 legacy single fire-cmd → no warnings (back-compat)
    T2 fanout-only with all-pass + 3 cmds + no deps → ok
    T3 fanout with cycle 0:1,1:0 → lint warns + runtime errors
    T4 fanout with quorum-5 but only 3 cmds → lint errors (impossible)
    T5 both fire-cmd AND fire-parallel-fanout present → lint warns (ambiguous; runtime prefers fanout)
@END

