  step-1 extend-parse-only
    add _parse_list_field helper + raw-line retention in _load_entry
    behavior: read fire-parallel-fanout but DO NOT dispatch yet
    test: legacy blockers fire identically; new field appears in introspection JSON
  step-2 add-parallel-dispatch-with-slot-pool
    implement spawn_async wrapper + slot-pool loop (max_concurrent=3 default)
    GAP wait_one_done — pick path-a (poll PIDs) for first cut, file FOLLOWUP for stdlib primitive
    flat dispatch (NO deps yet) — equivalent to fully-parallel with cap
  step-3 add-DAG-topo-and-cycle-detect
    cross-repo import parallel_scheduler.hexa OR copy topo_sort+has_cycle into hive/tool
    enforce ordering via slot-pool with predecessor-ready gate
  step-4 aggregate-verdict-and-sentinel
    implement match on aggregate + emit __BLOCKER_FANOUT_RESULT__
    raw-66 trailer on FAIL or unknown-aggregate
  step-5 audit-ledger-format-extension
    extend _build_log_line + JSONL writer with fanout_idx + fsm fields
    update blocker_autofire_lint.hexa with R1-R4 rules in same shard
@END

@R c3-honest-gaps-and-risks
  gap-1 wait_one_done() / proc_wait_any()
    not in hexa stdlib (verified by absence in tool/_init + ai_err)
    workaround: poll PIDs every N ms — adds wakeup overhead, NOT race-free
    proper fix: extend stdlib (separate FOLLOWUP shard)
  gap-2 parallel_scheduler.hexa cross-repo
    lives in hexa-lang, not hive — import path resolution unverified
    workaround: inline copy of topo_sort + has_cycle (~30 LOC) into blocker_autofire.hexa
  gap-3 _parse_list_field design
    current _load_entry strips empty lines + comments; list parsing needs
    indent-sensitive grouping → may need _load_entry refactor (risk of regressing legacy)
  gap-4 chflags-uchg
    file is uchg-locked → impl phase needs `chflags nouchg` + re-lock dance
    failure mode: forgot-to-relock leaves file mutable post-deploy
  own-11-strict no Clay-BT 'resolution' claims in this shard — sketch is design-intent only
  raw-91-C3 sketch only; zero file mutations performed; no claim of working code
@END
